	<h3 id="introduction"><b>Introduction</b></h3>
    <p style="text-align: justify">
        Data is the biggest superpower in the business world, and collecting data from time to time contributes to the growth of the business. Furthermore, this data collected is then used by data engineers for the enhancement of the customer service. Data engineers are responsible to build, implement, and support the Microsoft BI solution with the aim to achieve market requirements. This is why companies across the world are spending millions of dollars to <a href="/shortreads/the-skills-gap-is-costing-corporates-how-to-bridge-the-gap" target="_blank"><b>hire Machine Learning Engineer</b></a>. 
    </p>
    
    <h3 id="What-Azure"><b>What is Azure Data Engineer?</b></h3>
    
    <p style="text-align: justify;">
        Azure Data Engineers are responsible for data-oriented implementation tasks, offer provisioning data storage, manage to ingest batch and streaming data, transform the data, imply data retention policies, solve bottleneck issues, find obstacles in performance and also access external data. The demand for Azure Data Engineers is increasing gradually, and that calls for the skills training programs to train Data Engineers. 
    </p>
    
    <p style="text-align: justify;">
        Besides basic skills like programming language, coding, database management, analytical skills, an Azure Data Engineer should have a basic understanding of evolution of the data landscape and the way it impacts Data Engineers. An Azure Engineer should have the knowledge about the differences between on-premises and cloud data solutions. Furthermore, the engineer should also possess strong knowledge about the Azure services.  
    </p>
    
    <p style="text-align: justify;">
        According to the market requirements, an Azure Data Engineer should also have skills related to data warehousing, Database systems like SQL, and NoSQL, ETL tolls, Python, Scala, Machine Learning, and Java programming languages. The candidate should also have in-depth knowledge on data structures and algorithm. 
    </p>
    
    <h3 id="Candidate-Become-Azure"><b>How Can a Candidate Become Azure Data Engineer?</b></h3>
    
    <p style="text-align: justify;">
        A candidate can become a successful Data Engineer in Microsoft Azure only if he/she is skilled in Azure fundamentals. Furthermore, the aspiring candidate should also be prepared to clear two major exams necessary to achieve the data engineer job role. These major exams are DP-201 and DP-200. 
    </p>
    
    <p style="text-align: justify;">
        The best part is the availability of a role-based certification to become a Data Engineer in Azure platform. However, to clear this certification the candidate should have at least one year of experience in Data Engineering field.  
    </p>
    
    <p style="text-align: justify;">
        Becoming an Azure Data Engineer is worth the effort and time you invest in preparation. So, get ready for these two exams and make way for a better career option.  
    </p>
    
    
